text.section:
In this section:
"employee retirement system" means a plan:
established and maintained by an employer for the benefit of its employees; and
qualified under § 401(a), § 403, or § 457(b) of the Internal Revenue Code; and
"employee retirement system" does not include:
an individual retirement account or annuity under § 408 of the Internal Revenue Code;
a Roth individual retirement account under § 408A of the Internal Revenue Code;
a rollover individual retirement account;
a simplified employee pension under Internal Revenue Code § 408(k); or
an ineligible deferred compensation plan under § 457(f) of the Internal Revenue Code.
